OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FStaying dry
OL,6,Fwith largely clear skies at first, but
OL,7,Fhigh cloud gradually spreading in from
OL,8,Fthe west. Strong south to southwest
OL,9,Fwinds developing in the north and west.
OL,10,
OL,11,CSaturday:FIt will remain dry on
OL,12,FSaturday. Feeling a touch milder again
OL,13,Fwith some bright spells or hazy
OL,14,Fsunshine. Quite windy in the north and
OL,15,Fwest.
OL,16,
OL,17,COutlook for Sunday to Tuesday:FVariable
OL,18,Fcloud and bright spells on Sunday and
OL,19,FMonday with occasional spells of rain.
OL,20,FCloudy and windy with rain on Tuesday.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
